regexEvaluator.descriptionCdata: a062d1fc-7a56-4165-aebe-9ae21b4fcbc5.description=North American Numbering Plan (NANP) phone numbers.\nCountry Code and Area Code are optional. Each number group may be separated by spaces and/or a hyphen. The area code may be surrounded by parentheses. NANP rules for valid area codes and prefixes are enforced; for example, 999 is not a valid area code.\n Examples\: 857-1501, 1-650-857-1501, +1 (650) 857-1501, 6508571501
regexEvaluator.name: phone number (1-555-555-5555)
